EKITI – Projects worth N2.4 billion have been facilitated by the Senator representing Ekiti North Senatorial ,Senator Olubunmi Adetumbi to Ek­iti State in the last two years. The projects which includ­ed construction of roads, solar boreholes, blocks of classrooms and empower­ment were spread across 73 communities in Ekiti North . Specifically, Adetumbi , chieftain of the All Progres­sives Congress (APC) and chairman, Senate Commit­tee on National Planning, disclosed that 20 units of so­lar-powered boreholes, seven township road projects and 3,6 & 12-block of classrooms in six selected schools within constituents. Back-To-School Campaign:Tuition Fees, Levies Hamper Return Of… Back-To-School Campaign: Tuition Fees, Levies Hamper Resumption The senator’s Director of Operations, Chief Segun Adelugba who conducted journalists round the var­ious sites and locations of the projects in the five Local Governments areas Speaking through his Di­rector of Operations, Sen­ator Adetumbi explained that five erosion/ ecolog­ical projects, building of two- lock up shops and Three ICT training centres across four local governments of Ikole,Ilejemeje, Oye and Ido/ Osi councils, while projects in Moba local government are in the pipeline and will commence soon. The legislator disclosed that about N10 million was spent on scholarship awards to over 200 students in ter­tiary institutions , while about 300 artisans have been exposed to modern training to sharpen their expertises. Senator Adetumbi dis­closed that the feat was achieved through personal sacrifices to uplift his people and by intense networking with relevant federal gov­ernment’s agencies to bring dividends of democracy to his constituents.